						<div class="postbody">I think of thread hijacking as completely changing the subject. Like randomly in the middle of a thread, just say like that one guy : "online spam_ignore: url". If you don't know about that, there was a guy in one of these threads who would just randomly post links to online pharmacies, and it was really stupid and annoying. I think mr. Memblers made it so whenever he posted a link to an online spam_ignore, it would link to some dr. mario thing. It was quite humorous. That is thread hijacking. I don't think a conversation where the subject changes fluently as thread hijacking.</div>

					
